<paragraph blockId="34.[264,1322,1785,1891]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Three species of 
<taxonomicName box="[464,578,1785,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pyramica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[464,578,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Pyramica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been recorded from California, of which two are endemic and one is introduced from the Old World. These are rare, cryptobiotic ants, thought to be specialist predators on springtails and other small arthropods.
</paragraph>
